Explanatory Data Analysis¶

By Muhammed Jimoh¶

The following variables/features are strongly correlated:

    BorrowerRate, BorrowerAPR, and LenderYield

Hence, I will be using BorrowerAPR to represent the other two, though correlation doesn't necessary implies causation.

Univariate Analysis¶

The following variables will be considered for univariate analysis:¶

`LoanStatus, ProsperRating_Alpha, Term, BorrowerState, IncomeRange, Occupation, and ProperScore`

Is the dataset imbalanced?

  • Yes, the dataset is imbalanced with over one-third of the datset belonging to Completed.
  • Completed: 75.6%, Chargedoff: 20.53% and Defaulted: 3.87%

What is the mode for ProperRating (Alpha)?

  • The mode for ProperRating (Alpha) is D.

What category of loan term did majority of the borrower opted for?

  • Majority of the borrower opted the 36 months term loans.

What are the top five states borrowers reside in?

  • The top five states borrowers reside in are: CA, FL, NY, TX and IL

What are the top two income brackets for borrowers?

  • The top two income brackets for borrowers are: 25,000 USD - 49,000 USD, and 50,000 USD - 74,999 USD

What are the top three occupation of borrowers?

  • The top three occupation of borrowers are: Other, Profession and Computer Programmer

What is the mode of the ProperScore?

  • The mode of the prosperScore is 8.0

Bivariate Analysis¶

What can you infer from the relationship between LoanStatus and Term?

  • The 36 months loan term had the highest number of values as expected since the data is imbalanced.
  • Most tend to default on the 60 months loan as it is a long term loan.
  • Alos, the 60 months loan term have a significant amount of chargedoff as compared to others

What can you infer from the relationship between IncomeRange and Term?

  • People in the 25,000 USD - 49,000 USD, and 50,000 USD - 74,999 USD tend to borrow a lot.
  • People in the 1 USD - 24,000 USD default on loans alot, and have a significant amount of chargedoff.
  • People with IncomeRange greater than or equal to 25,000 USD had the highest count in terms of loan consideration. With majority being around 25,000 USD - 74,999 USD

Which category of ProperRating (Alpha) have the highest proportion of chargedoff?

  • The HR category of ProperRating (Alpha) have the highest proportion of chargedoff

ListingCategory: (Nominal Variable)

  • The category of the listing that the borrower selected when posting their listing:

    0 - Not Available, 1 - Debt Consolidation, 2 - Home Improvement, 3 - Business, 4 - Personal Loan, 5 - Student Use, 6 - Auto, 7- Other, 8 - Baby&Adoption, 9 - Boat, 10 - Cosmetic Procedure, 11 - Engagement Ring, 12 - Green Loans, 13 - Household Expenses, 14 - Large Purchases, 15 - Medical/Dental, 16 - Motorcycle, 17 - RV, 18 - Taxes, 19 - Vacation,20 - Wedding Loans,

What is the major reason for borrowing loans?

  • Most people's reason for borrowing loan is due to Debt Consolidation
  • Majority of the defaulters had oustanding debt already.

What are the major two occupation of borrowers?

  • The major two occupation of borrowers are Other, and Professional

Multivariate¶

What is the relationship between MonthlyLoanPayment and LoanOriginalAmount for the different loan terms?

  • The relationship between MonthlyLoanPayment and LoanOriginalAmount is a positive and increasing relationship, though the slope is steeper for different types of term.

How does BorrowerAPR impact the relationship between LoanStatus and EmploymentStatus?

  • Most people tend to default on a loan with higher BorrowerAPR as compared to loans with lower BorrowerApr regardless of their employement status.

What is the relationship between BorrowerAPR and ProperRating (Numeric) for the different LoanStatus category?

  • The ProperRating_Numeric exhibit a negative relationship with the BorrowerAPR regardless of the different loan status.

Are some variable pair strongly correlated?

  • The following pairs of variables are strongly positively correlated:

      [MonthlyLoanPayment, LoanOriginalAmount], [ProsperScore, ProsperRating_Numeric]

  • The following pairs of variable are strongly negatively correlated:

      [ProsperRating_Numeric, BorrowerAPR], [ProsperProsperScore, BorrowerRate],[ProsperProsperScore, BorrowerAPR]
